I've created the Image feature guide at `image.md`. The document covers:

- **Creating an ImageView** — Factory methods and URL configuration
- **Loading and Resource Management** — Async loading, load/release policies, synchronous loading, fast-track uploading, and placeholders
- **Fitting and Scaling** — FittingMode options, SamplingMode filters, and desired size hints
- **Image Color and Tinting** — Color multiplication with UiColor
- **Pixel Area and Sub-Regions** — Normalized coordinates and animatable pan/zoom effects
- **Animated Images** — AnimatedImageView for GIF playback with loop and frame control
- **Alpha Masking** — Mask URLs, crop-to-mask, and N-patch borders

All API examples are grounded in the public headers (`image-view.h`, `animated-image-view.h`, `image-enumerations.h`) and adapted from the sample files in `repos/dali-ui/samples/image-view/`.
